<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

<TR>
    <TD width="4%"></TD>
    <TD width="96%"></TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top">
    <TD>
    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">15.&#160;</FONT></B>
</TD>
    <TD>
    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">SUBSEQUENT
    EVENTS</FONT></B>
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    On February&#160;4, 2008, we entered into an agreement for an
    accelerated share repurchase (ASR) program with an affiliate of
    Merrill Lynch, Pierce, Fenner&#160;&#038; Smith Incorporated
    (Merrill Lynch). Under the agreement, we purchased
    12.5&#160;million shares of our outstanding common stock at
    $60.58 per share for a total purchase price of
    $757&#160;million. The repurchase was funded with internal
    capital. The shares were acquired as a part of previously
    announced share repurchase authorizations by our board of
    directors and will be held in treasury. Under the agreement,
    Merrill Lynch plans to purchase shares of our common stock in
    the open market from time to time until it has acquired a number
    of shares equivalent to the number of shares we purchased from
    Merrill Lynch. At the end of this period, we may receive, or may
    be required to remit, a purchase price adjustment based upon the
    volume weighted average price of our common stock during the ASR
    program period. Under the terms of the ASR, we may elect to
    receive or pay any settlement amount in cash or shares of our
    common stock at our option. The completion and settlement of the
    ASR program is expected to occur during the second quarter of
    2008, although the settlement may occur before the second
    quarter at Merrill Lynch&#146;s option.
</DIV>

<P align="center" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <BR>
    II-99
</DIV><!-- END PAGE WIDTH -->

<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="width: 94%; margin-left: 3%"><!-- BEGIN PAGE WIDTH -->
<P>
<DIV  align="left" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: times">
<A href="#998">
Table of Contents
</A>
</DIV><P>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

<TR>
    <TD width="10%"></TD>
    <TD width="90%"></TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top">
    <TD>
    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">ITEM&#160;9.&#160;&#160;</FONT></B>
</TD>
    <TD>
    <A name='114'></A><B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">CHANGES
    IN AND DISAGREEMENTS WITH ACCOUNTANTS ON ACCOUNTING AND
    FINANCIAL DISCLOSURE.</FONT></B>
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    There have been no changes in, or disagreements with,
    accountants on accounting and financial disclosure matters
    during the years ended December&#160;31, 2007 and 2006.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 24pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>
<A name='115'>
<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">ITEM&#160;9A.&#160;&#160;CONTROLS
    AND PROCEDURES.</FONT></B>
</DIV>
</A>
<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">Disclosure
    Controls and Procedures</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    The Company&#146;s management, with the participation of the
    Company&#146;s Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial
    Officer, has evaluated the effectiveness of the Company&#146;s
    disclosure controls and procedures (as such term is defined in
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">Rules&#160;13a-15(e)</FONT>
    and
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">15d-15(e)</FONT>
    under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the
    &#147;Exchange Act&#148;)) as of the end of the period covered
    by this annual report (the &#147;Evaluation Date&#148;). Based
    on such evaluation, the Company&#146;s Chief Executive Officer
    and Chief Financial Officer have concluded that, as of the
    Evaluation Date, the Company&#146;s disclosure controls and
    procedures are effective.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">Internal Control
    Over Financial Reporting</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    (a)&#160;<U>Management&#146;s Annual Report on Internal Control
    Over Financial Reporting.</U>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    Management&#146;s Annual Report on Internal Control Over
    Financial Reporting is incorporated herein by reference from
    Part&#160;II, Item&#160;8 of this report.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    (b)&#160;<U>Attestation Report of the Registered Public
    Accounting Firm.</U>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    The Attestation Report of the Registered Public Accounting Firm
    on internal control over financial reporting is incorporated
    herein by reference from Part&#160;II, Item&#160;8 of this
    report.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    (c)&#160;<U>Changes in Internal Control Over Financial
    Reporting.</U>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    There have not been any changes in the Company&#146;s internal
    control over financial reporting (as such term is defined in
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">Rules&#160;13a-15(f)</FONT>
    and
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">15d-15(f)</FONT>
    under the Exchange Act) during the last fiscal quarter of 2007
    that have materially affected, or are reasonably likely to
    materially affect, the Company&#146;s internal control over
    financial reporting.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 24pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>
<A name='116'>
<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">ITEM&#160;9B.&#160;&#160;OTHER
    INFORMATION.</FONT></B>
</DIV>
</A>
<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    Not applicable.
</DIV>

<P align="center" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <BR>
    II-101
</DIV><!-- END PAGE WIDTH -->
<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="width: 94%; margin-left: 3%"><!-- BEGIN PAGE WIDTH -->
<P>
<DIV  align="left" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: times">
<A href="#998">
Table of Contents
</A>
</DIV><P>
<A name='117'>
<DIV style="margin-top: 18pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="center" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">PART&#160;III</FONT></B>
</DIV>
</A>
<DIV style="margin-top: 18pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    Pursuant to General Instruction&#160;G to
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">Form&#160;10-K,</FONT>
    Items&#160;10 through 14 are incorporated by reference from the
    Company&#146;s definitive Notice and Proxy Statement relating to
    the Company&#146;s 2008 Annual Meeting of Shareholders, which
    will be filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission on or
    about March&#160;20, 2008, pursuant to Regulation&#160;14A under
    the Exchange Act. The Audit Committee Report and Compensation
    Committee Report to be included in such proxy statement shall be
    deemed to be furnished in this report and shall not be
    incorporated by reference into any filing under the Securities
    Act of 1933 as a result of such furnishing in Items&#160;11 and
    12, respectively.
</DIV>

<DIV  align="left" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: times">
<A href="#998">
Table of Contents
</A>
</DIV><P>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    (c)&#160;<U>FINANCIAL STATEMENT SCHEDULES</U>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 36pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>
<A name='309'>
<DIV style="margin-top: 18pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="center" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">REPORT OF
    INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV align="center" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <B>ON FINANCIAL STATEMENT SCHEDULES</B>
</DIV>
</A>

<DIV style="margin-top: 24pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    The shareholders and board of directors of Aflac Incorporated:
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    Under date of February&#160;28, 2008, we reported on the
    consolidated balance sheets of Aflac Incorporated and
    subsidiaries (the Company) as of December&#160;31, 2007, and
    2006, and the related consolidated statements of earnings,
    shareholders&#146; equity, cash flows, and comprehensive income
    for each of the years in the three-year period ended
    December&#160;31, 2007, which are included herein. In connection
    with our audits of the aforementioned consolidated financial
    statements, we also audited the related financial statement
    schedules as listed in Item&#160;15. These financial statement
    schedules are the responsibility of the Company&#146;s
    management. Our responsibility is to express an opinion on these
    financial statement schedules based on our audits.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    In our opinion, such financial statement schedules, when
    considered in relation to the basic consolidated financial
    statements taken as a whole, present fairly, in all material
    respects, the information set forth therein.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    As discussed in Note&#160;1 to the consolidated financial
    statements, the Company adopted the provisions of Staff
    Accounting Bulletin&#160;No.&#160;108, <I>Considering the
    Effects of Prior Year Misstatements when Quantifying
    Misstatements in Current Year Financial Statements, </I>as of
    January&#160;1, 2006. Additionally, as discussed in Notes&#160;1
    and 12 to the consolidated financial statements, the Company
    adopted Statement of Financial Accounting Standards
    No.&#160;158, <I>Employers&#146; Accounting for Defined Benefit
    Pension and Other Postretirement Plans, an amendment of FASB
    Statements No.&#160;87, 88, 106 and 132(R), </I>as of
    December&#160;31, 2006.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 48pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <IMG src="g11443g1144302.gif" alt="(-s- KPMG LLP)">
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 36pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    Atlanta, Georgia<BR>
    February&#160;28, 2008
</DIV>

<P align="center" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

<DIV align="center" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">SCHEDULE&#160;II<BR>
    CONDENSED FINANCIAL INFORMATION OF REGISTRANT<BR>
    <BR>
    </FONT></B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">Aflac
    Incorporated (Parent Only)<BR>
    Notes to Condensed Financial Statements

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    The accompanying condensed financial statements should be read
    in conjunction with the consolidated financial statements and
    notes thereto of Aflac Incorporated and Subsidiaries included in
    Part&#160;II, Item&#160;8 of this report.

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <TD width="4%"></TD>
    <TD width="96%"></TD>

<TR valign="top">
    <TD>
    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">(A)&#160;</FONT></B>
</TD>
    <TD>
    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">Notes
    Payable</FONT></B>
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<DIV style="margin-top: 9pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    A summary of notes payable as of December 31 follows:
</DIV>

<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

<TR>
    <TD width="4%"></TD>
    <TD width="96%"></TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top">
    <TD>
    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">(B)&#160;</FONT></B>
</TD>
    <TD>
    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">Derivatives</FONT></B>
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    We have only limited activity with derivative financial
    instruments. We do not use them for trading purposes nor do we
    engage in leveraged derivative transactions. The Parent Company
    has contracts
</DIV>

<P align="center" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <BR>
    IV-10
</DIV><!-- END PAGE WIDTH -->
<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>

<DIV style="width: 94%; margin-left: 3%"><!-- BEGIN PAGE WIDTH -->

</A>
</DIV><P>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    for cross-currency swaps related to its senior notes payable and
    interest rate swaps related to its variable interest rate
    Uridashi notes. For further information regarding these
    derivatives, see Notes&#160;1 and 4 of the Notes to the
    Consolidated Financial Statements.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

    <TD width="96%"></TD>

<TR valign="top">
    <TD>
    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">(C)&#160;</FONT></B>
</TD>
    <TD>
    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">Income
    Taxes</FONT></B>
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<DIV style="margin-top: 9pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    The Company and its eligible U.S.&#160;subsidiaries file a
    consolidated U.S.&#160;federal income tax return. Income tax
    liabilities or benefits are recorded by each principal
    subsidiary based upon separate return calculations, and any
    difference between the consolidated provision and the aggregate
    amounts recorded by the subsidiaries is reflected in the Parent
    Company financial statements. For further information on income
    taxes, see Note&#160;8 of the Notes to the Consolidated
    Financial Statements.
</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <I><FONT style="font-size: 10pt">See the accompanying Report of
    Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm.</FONT></I>
</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <I><FONT style="font-size: 10pt">Segment amounts may not agree
    in total to the corresponding consolidated amounts due to
    rounding.</FONT></I>
</DIV>

<P align="center" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <BR>
    IV-12
</DIV><!-- END PAGE WIDTH -->

<DOCUMENT>
<TYPE>EX-10.3
<SEQUENCE>2
<FILENAME>g11443exv10w3.htm
<DESCRIPTION>EX-10.3 FOURTH AMENDMENT TO AFLAC SUPPLEMENTAL EXECUTIVE RETIREMENT PLAN
<TEXT>
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>EX-10.3 FOURTH AMENDMENT TO EXEC. RETIREMENT PLAN</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="width: 94%; margin-left: 3%"><!-- BEGIN PAGE WIDTH -->
<P>
<DIV align="left" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: sans-serif">
<A href="g11443e10vk.htm">
Aflac Incorporated 2007 Form 10-K
</A>
</DIV><P>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">EXHIBIT&#160;10.3</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 18pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="center" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">FOURTH AMENDMENT
    TO THE AFLAC INCORPORATED<BR>
    SUPPLEMENTAL EXECUTIVE RETIREMENT PLAN<BR>
    (as amended and restated effective January&#160;1,
    2001)</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    This Amendment to the Aflac Incorporated Supplemental Executive
    Retirement Plan, as amended and restated effective
    January&#160;1, 2001, is adopted by Aflac Incorporated (the
    &#147;Company&#148;), effective as of December&#160;6, 2007 (the
    &#147;Amendment Date&#148;).
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 18pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="center" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">WITNESSETH:</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <B>WHEREAS</B>, the Company maintains the AFLAC Incorporated
    Supplemental Executive Retirement Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;)
    for the benefit of certain key management and highly compensated
    employees;&#160;and
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <B>WHEREAS</B>, pursuant to Section&#160;7.1 of the Plan, the
    Compensation Committee of the Board of Directors of the Company
    (the &#147;Committee&#148;) has the right to amend the Plan at
    any time;&#160;and
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <B>WHEREAS</B>, the Committee desires to amend the Plan to allow
    participants to elect a form of payment available under the
    Aflac Incorporated Pension Plan with respect to the
    participant&#146;s benefits that are subject to
    Section&#160;409A of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as
    amended, which is generally the participant&#146;s benefits that
    accrued
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">and/or</FONT>
    became vested after December&#160;31, 2004;
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <B>NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED</B>, that the Plan is hereby
    amended as follows, effective as of the Amendment Date:
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    1.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;A new Section&#160;1.32A shall
    be added to the Plan, to read as follows:
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 11%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    1.32A <B><U>Post-409A Benefit</U> </B>means, with respect to a
    Participant, his benefits under the Plan other than his Pre-409A
    Benefit.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    2.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;A new Section&#160;1.32B shall
    be added to the Plan, to read as follows:
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 11%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    1.32B <B><U>Pre-409A </U></B>Benefit shall mean the present
    value of the portion of a Participant&#146;s Annual Retirement
    Benefit (if any) that he would have been entitled to receive if
    he had voluntarily terminated services without Cause and not due
    to death on December&#160;31, 2004, and received a payment of
    benefits available from the Plan on the earliest possible date
    allowed under the Plan to receive a payment of benefits
    following the termination of services, in the form with the
    maximum value, including any benefits already paid or in pay
    status. The Pre-409A Benefit may increase to equal the present
    value of the benefit the Participant actually becomes entitled
    to, in the form and at the time actually paid, determined under
    the terms of the Plan (including applicable limits under the
    Internal Revenue Code), as in effect on October&#160;3, 2004,
    without regard to any further services rendered by the
    Participant after December&#160;31, 2004, or any other events
    affecting the amount of or the entitlement to benefits, other
    than the Participant&#146;s election with respect to the time or
    form of the benefit.
</DIV>

<P align="center" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <BR>
    EXH 10.3-1
</DIV><!-- END PAGE WIDTH -->
<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<P><HR noshade><P>
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="width: 94%; margin-left: 3%"><!-- BEGIN PAGE WIDTH -->
<P>
<DIV align="left" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: sans-serif">
<A href="g11443e10vk.htm">
Aflac Incorporated 2007 Form 10-K
</A>
</DIV><P>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">

<TR>
    <TD width="6%"></TD>
    <TD width="94%"></TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <TD>    3.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</TD>
    <TD align="left">
    Section&#160;3.6(c) of the Plan is deleted in its entirety, and
    a new Section&#160;3.6(c) is added to read as follows:
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 11%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    (c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<B><U>Optional Form of
    Payment.</U></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 17%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    (i)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<B><U>Pre-409A Benefit</U></B>.
    A Participant may elect, not later than 3&#160;months before his
    termination of employment with the Company and all Affiliates,
    to have his
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">Pre-409A</FONT>
    Benefit paid in the form of a Joint and 50% Survivor Annuity,
    which shall be the Actuarial Equivalent of the
    Participant&#146;s Pre-409A Benefit payable in the form of a
    Single Life Annuity. Notwithstanding any such election, if a
    Participant who has elected a Joint and 50% Survivor Annuity is
    not married on the date of his termination of employment, his
    Pre-409A Benefit shall be paid in the form of a Single Life
    Annuity.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 17%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    (ii)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<B><U>Post-409A
    Benefit</U></B>.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 17%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 6%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    (A)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;A Participant whose Post-409A
    Benefit is payable in a life annuity (as that term is defined in
    Treasury Regulation&#160;Section 1.409A-2(b)(2)(ii)(A)) and who
    has not yet attained his Benefit Commencement Date may elect to
    change the form of payment of his Post-409A Benefit to another
    type of life annuity (as that term is defined in Treasury
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">Regulation&#160;Section&#160;1.409A-2(b)(2)(ii)(A))</FONT>
    that is permitted under the Pension Plan (based on the terms of
    the Pension Plan in effect on the date of the election). The
    newly elected life annuity shall have the same scheduled date
    for the first annuity payment and shall be Actuarially
    Equivalent to the Participant&#146;s Post-409A Benefit payable
    in the form of a Single Life Annuity. An election shall only be
    permitted under this subsection if the annuity form of payment
    in effect for the Participant&#146;s Post-409A Benefit prior to
    the change and the annuity form of payment elected are
    actuarially equivalent applying reasonable actuarial methods and
    assumptions as described in Treasury
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">Section&#160;1.409A-2(b)(2)(ii).</FONT>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 17%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 6%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    (B)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;As of December&#160;6, 2007,
    the life annuities as defined in Treasury
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">Regulation&#160;Section&#160;1.409A-2(b)(2)(ii)(A)</FONT>
    among which a Participant may choose pursuant to this subsection
    are the following: (i)&#160;Single Life Annuity; (ii)&#160;joint
    and 50% survivor annuity; (iii)&#160;joint and 75% survivor
    annuity; and (iv)&#160;joint and 100% survivor annuity. (The
    other forms of distribution offered under the Pension Plan as of
    said date do not qualify as actuarially equivalent life
    annuities for purposes of Code Section&#160;409A and may not be
    selected.)
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    4.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Except as amended herein, the
    Plan shall continue in full force and effect.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 4%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <B>IN WITNESS WHEREOF</B>, Aflac Incorporated has caused this
    Amendment to the Plan to be executed on the date shown below.
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 24pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 49%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <B>AFLAC INCORPORATED</B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 49%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

</DIV>

    M. Loudermilk</DIV><BR>
    <DIV style="font-size: 2pt; margin-left: 0%; width: 100%;border-bottom: 1pt solid #000000"></DIV><!-- callerid=115 iwidth=251 length=0 -->

<DOCUMENT>
<TYPE>EX-10.8
<SEQUENCE>3
<FILENAME>g11443exv10w8.htm
<DESCRIPTION>EX-10.8 AFLAC INCORPORATED SALES INCENTIVE PLAN
<TEXT>
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>EX-10.8 AFLAC INCORPORATED SALES INCENTIVE PLAN</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="width: 94%; margin-left: 3%"><!-- BEGIN PAGE WIDTH -->
<P>
<DIV align="left" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: sans-serif">
<A href="g11443e10vk.htm">
Aflac Incorporated 2007 Form 10-K
</A>
</DIV><P>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">EXHIBIT&#160;10.8</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 18pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="center" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">Aflac
    Incorporated Sales Incentive Plan</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    Aflac maintains an unwritten Sales Incentive Plan (SIP) under
    which the Director of Sales of Aflac is a participant. The SIP
    provides for performance-based bonuses based on the achievement
    of new annualized premium sales growth and field force
    development objectives. The targets for each objective are
    determined at the beginning of the performance period (typically
    the calendar year). Bonuses under the SIP are determined based
    on performance achievement results at the conclusion of the
    performance period.
</DIV>

<P align="center" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <BR>
    EXH 10.8-1
</DIV><!-- END PAGE WIDTH -->
</BODY>
</HTML>
</TEXT>
</DOCUMENT>

<DESCRIPTION>EX-10.33 AFLAC CONSULTING ARRANGEMENT
<TEXT>
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>EX-10.33 AFLAC CONSULTING ARRANGEMENT</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="width: 94%; margin-left: 3%"><!-- BEGIN PAGE WIDTH -->
<P>
<DIV align="left" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: sans-serif">
<A href="g11443e10vk.htm">
Aflac Incorporated 2007 Form 10-K
</A>
</DIV><P>
</DIV><!-- END PAGE WIDTH -->
<DIV style="width: 94%; margin-left: 3%"><!-- BEGIN PAGE WIDTH -->

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 5%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">EXHIBIT&#160;10.33</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 18pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="center" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">Aflac Consulting
    Arrangement with E. Stephen Purdom</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    In the fourth quarter of 2007, Aflac entered into a consulting
    arrangement with Mr.&#160;E. Stephen Purdom, an independent
    member of Aflac Incorporated&#146;s board of directors.
    Mr.&#160;Purdom has been retained as a special consultant for
    the purpose of helping Aflac Japan with: (1)&#160;marketing and
    sales force development and (2)&#160;underwriting and claims.
    The term of the agreement is for the fourth quarter of 2007 and
    the first two quarters of 2008. The compensation has been
    established at $40,000 per quarter.
</DIV>

<P align="center" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <BR>
    EXH 10.33-1
</DIV><!-- END PAGE WIDTH -->
</BODY>

<DESCRIPTION>EX-31.1 SECTION 302, CERTIFICATION OF THE CEO
<TEXT>
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>EX-31.1 SECTION 302, CERTIFICATION OF THE CEO</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!-- PAGEBREAK -->
<H5 align="left" style="page-break-before:always">&nbsp;</H5><P>

<DIV style="width: 94%; margin-left: 3%"><!-- BEGIN PAGE WIDTH -->
<P>
<DIV align="left" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: sans-serif">
<A href="g11443e10vk.htm">
Aflac Incorporated 2007 Form 10-K
</A>
</DIV><P>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">EXHIBIT&#160;31.1</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="center" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica">Certification
    of Chief Executive Officer</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    I, Daniel P. Amos, certify that:
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    1.&#160;I have reviewed this annual report on
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">Form&#160;10-K</FONT>
    of Aflac Incorporated;
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    2.&#160;Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any
    untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material
    fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the
    circumstances under which such statements were made, not
    misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    3.&#160;Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and
    other financial information included in this report, fairly
    present in all material respects the financial condition,
    results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of,
    and for, the periods presented in this report;
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    4.&#160;The registrant&#146;s other certifying officer and I are
    responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls
    and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">Rules&#160;13a-15(e)</FONT>
    and
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">15d-15(e))</FONT>
    and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in
    Exchange Act
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">Rules&#160;13a-15(f)</FONT>
    and
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">15d-15(f))</FONT>
    for the registrant and have:
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">

<TR>
    <TD width="3%"></TD>
    <TD width="3%"></TD>
    <TD width="94%"></TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>    a)&#160;
</TD>
    <TD align="left">
    Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such
    disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our
    supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the
    registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made
    known to us by others within those entities, particularly during
    the period in which this report is being prepared;
</TD>
</TR>


<TR style="line-height: 6pt; font-size: 1pt"><TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>


<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>    b)&#160;
</TD>
    <TD align="left">
    Designed such internal control over financial reporting, or
    caused such internal control over financial reporting to be
    designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable assurance
    regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the
    preparation of financial statements for external purposes in
    accordance with generally accepted accounting principles;
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">

<TR>
    <TD width="3%"></TD>
    <TD width="3%"></TD>
    <TD width="94%"></TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>    c)&#160;
</TD>
    <TD align="left">
    Evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant&#146;s disclosure
    controls and procedures and presented in this report our
    conclusions about the effectiveness of the disclosure controls
    and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this
    report based on such evaluation;&#160;and
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">

<TR>
    <TD width="3%"></TD>
    <TD width="3%"></TD>
    <TD width="94%"></TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>    d)&#160;
</TD>
    <TD align="left">
    Disclosed in this report any change in the registrant&#146;s
    internal control over financial reporting that occurred during
    the registrant&#146;s most recent fiscal quarter (the
    registrant&#146;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual
    report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to
    materially affect, the registrant&#146;s internal control over
    financial reporting;&#160;and
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    5.&#160;The registrant&#146;s other certifying officer and I
    have disclosed, based on our most recent evaluation of internal
    control over financial reporting, to the registrant&#146;s
    auditors and the audit committee of the registrant&#146;s board
    of directors (or persons performing the equivalent functions):
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 6pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">

<TR>
    <TD width="3%"></TD>
    <TD width="3%"></TD>
    <TD width="94%"></TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>    a)&#160;
</TD>
    <TD align="left">
    All significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the
    design or operation of internal control over financial reporting
    which are reasonably likely to adversely affect the
    registrant&#146;s ability to record, process, summarize and
    report financial information;&#160;and
</TD>
</TR>


<TR style="line-height: 6pt; font-size: 1pt"><TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>


<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>    b)&#160;
</TD>
    <TD align="left">
    Any fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or
    other employees who have a significant role in the
    registrant&#146;s internal control over financial reporting.
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<DIV style="margin-top: 9pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV style="width: 94%; margin-left: 3%"><!-- BEGIN PAGE WIDTH -->
<P>
<DIV align="left" style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: sans-serif">
<A href="g11443e10vk.htm">
Aflac Incorporated 2007 Form 10-K
</A>
</DIV><P>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

    <B><FONT style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica">EXHIBIT&#160;32</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 18pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="center" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; font-size: 14pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">

    <B><FONT style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica">Certification
    of CEO and CFO Pursuant to<BR>
    18&#160;U.S.C. Section&#160;1350,<BR>
    as Adopted Pursuant to<BR>
    Section&#160;906 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002</FONT></B>
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    In connection with the Annual Report on
    <FONT style="white-space: nowrap">Form&#160;10-K</FONT>
    of Aflac Incorporated (the &#147;Company&#148;) for the annual
    period ended December&#160;31, 2007, as filed with the
    Securities and Exchange Commission on the date hereof (the
    &#147;Report&#148;), Daniel P. Amos, as Chief Executive Officer
    of the Company, and Kriss Cloninger III, as Chief Financial
    Officer of the Company, each hereby certifies, pursuant to
    18&#160;U.S.C. Section&#160;1350, as adopted pursuant to
    Section&#160;906 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002, that, to the
    best of his knowledge:
</DIV>

<DIV style="margin-top: 12pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">

<TR>
    <TD width="4%"></TD>
    <TD width="4%"></TD>
    <TD width="92%"></TD>
</TR>

<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>    (1)&#160;
</TD>
    <TD align="left">
    The Report fully complies with the requirements of
    Section&#160;13(a) or 15(d) of the Securities Exchange Act of
    1934;&#160;and
</TD>
</TR>


<TR style="line-height: 12pt; font-size: 1pt"><TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>


<TR valign="top" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
    <TD>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD>    (2)&#160;
</TD>
    <TD align="left">
    The information contained in the Report fairly presents, in all
    material respects, the financial condition and results of
    operations of the Company.
</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

<DIV style="margin-top: 48pt; font-size: 1pt">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV align="left" style="margin-left: 0%; margin-right: 0%; text-indent: 0%; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica; color: #000000; background: #FFFFFF">
